narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you get the wonderful opportunity to take this class, you MUST take it. Honestly the chance of a lifetime.
I would recommend this class without reservation. An overview of Shakespeare's best works, led by one of the most incisive intellectual minds of our time.
The best part of my semester.

This course is a unique opportunity to discuss a most fascinating subject with perhaps the most brilliant professor at Yale. Professor Bloom lives up to every bit of his reputation. He is engaging and thoughtful about the material. And it's difficult to convey how life-changing the course has been.
